h2 Icons
p.-text
  | To add icons to a textarea, wrap the input in a <code>div</code> using the class <code>m-input__wrapper</code>.
  | Next, add the icon as a sibling of the <code>textarea</code> and use an icon alignment utility class
  | (e.g. <code>-icon--left</code>) to specify where it should be placed.

h3 Left Aligned
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-form__item(style="max-width:30rem")
      label.a-label(for="example__icon-left") Label
      .m-input__wrapper.-icon--left
        textarea.a-input(id="example__icon-left") Sample text
        i.a-icon.icon-map-marker.-text--muted
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-form__item">
      <label class="a-label" for="example__icon-left">Label</label>
      <div class="m-input__wrapper -icon--left">
        <textarea class="a-input" id="example__icon-left">
          Sample text
        </textarea>
        <i class="a-icon icon-map-marker -text--muted"></i>
      </div>
    </div>

